-- FACTBOX: Hewlett-Packard in talks to buy rival EDS
-- 
-- Mon May 12, 2008 7:29pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/12/us-eds-hewlettpackard-factbox-idUSN1250636320080512

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - Hewlett-Packard Co ( HPQ.N ) is in talks to buy technology outsourcing company Electronic Data Systems Corp EDS.N for $12 billion to $13 billion in a deal that would vault it to a close second to IBM in technology services. 

 Below are annual revenue and computer services revenue figures for IBM, HP, and EDS: F2007 F2006 HP total revs $104.3 billion $91.7 billion IBM total revs $98.8 billion $91.4 billion EDS total revs $22.1 billion $21.3 billion F2007 Market share F2006 Pct growth IBM services revs $54.1 billion 7.2 $48.2 billion 12.2 HP+EDS services $39.4 5.3 $37.4 billion 5.2 HP services $17.3 2.3 $16.0 billion 8.1 EDS services $22.1 3.0 $21.4 billion 3.4 Source: company annual reports, market research firm Gartner Inc (Reporting by  Duncan Martell ; Editing by  Braden Reddall )